TextBlock.TextLine: The stock market Tuesday moved up raggedly, clinch
ing a sizable gain for October and more than wiping
out the September loss. Trading was moderate.
The story of the day was like the story of the month
a two-way market with some good gains and some
sharp losses. Despite continued shifts in portfolios for
tax purposes, the trend was upward.
The market's ability to respond to bullish news was
reflected by eagerness to buy Republic Aviation, the
most active stock, up two at 50V6 on 36,500 shares. On
top of sharply higher earnings, this company proposed
Symptomatic of reasonably founded doubt about
the progress of the economic upturn was U. S. Steel
which closed unchanged after erasing a fractional gain.
The steels were fairly buoyant early In the day but
backed away from their best prices In late trading. After
the close U. S. steel announced lower quarterly earnings
compared with a year ago and also the previous quarter.
